<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
On roadsides around 1200 m in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
in the same general area as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fissifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea fissifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Aguililla, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
J. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="González">Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
et al.
</emphasis>
412 (IEB); ibid., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Carranza &amp; I. Silva</emphasis>
6665 (IEB)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The corolla is suburceolate resembling that of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is maroon in colour and the inflorescence is secund, not cymose as stated in the protologue. It is distinguished by the corolla colour, much longer secondary peduncles to 25 mm (not 12 mm) and longer sepal awns.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
